## Contracts `[FIXED]`

All JSON. All in `cron/contracts/`.

- `user-contract.json` вАФ permanent. Goals, journeys, two quality bars (technical + product). Every criterion has calibration (fail/pass/high_pass). Sacred вАФ never weaken.
- `sprint-{N}/contract.json` вАФ per-sprint metadata + deliverable list.
- `sprint-{N}/deliverables/*.json` вАФ one per deliverable. Independent. Description + verifier (description, qualitative, test pointer, calibration).
- `sprint-{N}/round-{M}/executor/*.json` вАФ what each executor built.
- `sprint-{N}/round-{M}/verifier/*.json` вАФ score + evidence + live_test + bugs per deliverable.
- `sprint-{N}/round-{M}/_summary.json` вАФ aggregate scores, pass/fail verdict.

## Principles `[FIXED]`

1. **Deliverables, not implementation** вАФ specify WHAT, never HOW
2. **10x capability** вАФ assume generators are 10x more capable than you'd guess
3. **Calibrated verification** вАФ every criterion has fail/pass/high_pass examples
4. **Live E2E testing** вАФ verifiers test the RUNNING app, not just read code
5. **Qualitative + quantitative** вАФ verifiers assess how it FEELS, not just if tests pass
6. **Loop until clean** вАФ rounds continue until ALL deliverables pass. No fixed count.
7. **Independent parallelism** вАФ up to 15 deliverables, each independent, all executed + verified in parallel
8. **User contract is sacred** вАФ checked every verify round. Never weaken, only strengthen.
9. **Every bug prevents its class** вАФ type > lint > gate > test > explorer
10. **User prompts are interrupts** вАФ drop everything when the operator speaks

